CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1945, pg. 2 reads: "Underground Palace - Three of the four small children who live in this cellar home with their mother smile happily for cameraman. Note electric wires, rude partitions... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Three children, including baby wearing light colored dress seated on bed with chenille bedspread, in basement apartment with bare light bulb and exposed pipes and wires, Tannehill Street
